<div id="outline-container-orgdece740" class="outline-3 learn">
<h3 id="orgdece740">For loops</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-orgdece740">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Repetitively typing the same code again and again is boring and can make your code very long.</li>
<li>In programming languages, repetitions make use of looping, formally, <b>iteration</b>, which we can use to cut out our reptitive code</li>
<li><b>for loops</b> are for fixed number of repetitions. For example, we need to draw a set number of the same circle in our previous exercises</li>
<li><p>
In python,  <b>for loops</b> can be used in the following ways:
</p>

<iframe src="https://trinket.io/embed/python/e74de5d00c" width="100%" height="600" frameborder="0" marginwidth="0" marginheight="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

