<div id="outline-container-org306d5d6" class="outline-3 learn">
<h3 id="org306d5d6">While loops</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org306d5d6">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>In python, we have learned that <b>for loops</b> can be used to repeat a block of code for a set number of times.</li>
<li>There is another kind of loop called <b>while loop</b> that will repeat a block code based on a set condition. As long as the condition is true, the block of code indented under it will be executed</li>
</ul>
<p>
For example the following will print "Hello world!" for ever!
</p>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-Python">
A = True
while A:
    print("Hello world!")

</pre>
</div>

<ul class="org-ul">
<li>This kind of loop can be very useful when we don't know how many repetitions we need. For example, you can play a game for as long as you want until you press quit or exit button.
This can be simulated as following:</li>
</ul>

<iframe src="https://trinket.io/embed/python/c3bdbf9460" width="100%" height="600" frameborder="0" marginwidth="0" marginheight="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
</div>
</div>
